<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When the developer creates a Zend_Form_Element of type 'file', it is not possible for him/her to retrieve the path that is inputted by the user.  Instead, Zend_Form_Element::getValue() returns the destination location.</p>

<p>It would be nice if the developer could get the original file path.</p>

<p>To reproduce:</p>

<p>1) Create a Zend_Form_Element of type 'file' i.e $this-&gt;createElement ( 'file', 'file' ).</p>

<p>2) Submit the form, and call: $form-&gt;file-&gt;getValue().</p>

<h1>intuitively, you would imagine that this would give you the value that the user inputted, not the destination location.</h1>

